The South African Reserve Bank cuts interest rates by 100 basis points to 4.25%. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) of theÂ South African Reserve Bank (SARB) has cut the interest rate by 100 basis points. This takes the repo rate to 4.25% per annum. South Africa is already in recession and the cut has the potential to weaken the rand.  eNCA's Devan Murugan has more details in the video above.